EMALAHLENI Mpumalanga police are searching for two suspects linked to a cash-in-transit robbery at a petrol station in Tasbet Park, eMalahleni (formerly Witbank).The incident occurred on Tuesday morning and was captured on CCTV.The footage shows a guard walking towards the back of a G4S truck after collecting cash from the filling station, unaware that he is being followed by two armed men.The men pounce on the guard as he enters the truck. The suspects took the guard s firearm and an undisclosed amount of money. The suspects fled the scene in a white Mazda that was parked nearby. We are investigating a case of armed robbery and we are appealing to members of public to assist us with information, said Mpumalanga police spokesman Brigadier Leonard Hlathi.Hlathi said nobody was injured during this incident.eNCA